Czech Stocks: Central European Media, Telefonica Czech Republic

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-09-13T15:06:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/czech-stocks-central-european-media-telefonica-czech-republic.html
The  Czech Republic ’s PX stock index
was little changed at 946.6 at its 4:28 p.m. close in Prague.  The following were among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Telefonica Czech Republic AS (SPTT CP) declined 1.3 percent
to 382 koruna, its second day of losses. The country’s biggest
phone operator was cut to “hold” from “accumulate” and had
its share-price estimate lowered to 379 koruna from 441 koruna
at Cyrrus.  Central European Media Enterprises Ltd. (CETV)   rose 1.9
percent to 180 koruna. The stock earlier rallied as much as 5.8
percent after the broadcaster said today Chief Financial Officer
David Sach bought 20,000 shares.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  